      "content": "The \"academic debate\" thing is exactly what they want people to think. It was a deliberate scrubbing of the records during the annexation. I actually have scans of the 1952 Treaty of Tashkent which clearly outlines the Aethelgard protectorate's borders and its seat in the precursor UN assemblies. If I want to formally challenge the current territorial claims by the neighboring states, what specific international legal mechanisms or protocols should I use to present these documents so they can't just be dismissed as \"unverified\"?",
